Police are looking for a man who has absconded from prison while serving a life sentence for murder.Daniel Barker, 34, who was jailed while a teenager in 2005, was reported missing from Hollesley Bay prison near Woodbridge, Suffolk, on Thursday morning after he missed a roll call.A Suffolk Police spokesperson said he had links with the Bradford area.He has been described as white, skinny and 5ft 5in tall, with short dark hair and a scar on the crown of his head.
Police have urged anyone who might have information about his potential whereabouts to contact them by calling 101.
